    <item>
      <title>20k problem with auras &amp; mounts</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&amp;message.id=12149#M12149</link>
      <description>&lt;br&gt;As some of you know, with Auras came the risk of death due to a bug if you were on a mount and moving too quickly. I found the problem with this code, but unfortunately it's too late to get proper testing of the fix before the next update though so for the time being please be careful of using auras and mounts at the same time. The change is pretty deep in the collision/movement system and we've learned to be extremely careful about making last minute changes to these sorts of things. We'll get the code on Test server ASAP however.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Just wanted to let folks know what was up with this one, I'm sure it affects a lot of people. For the short term, if you want to avoid risking this bug, just don't use both at the same time. I'm certain this will be fixed in the update after this next one. It's risky to put in core level changes like this at the last minute and despite what some might think we do try to test as carefully as possible and this, unfortunately, would be cutting it too close.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For those wondering, the movement system was not excluding the aura NPC from movement, you were basically being deflected off of the aura. Auras should have been ignored for movement, and they are unless you are on a mount - the bug was that while mounted you actually did collide with them. Since auras are always centered exactly upon your player, the&#xD;
movement deflection logic had a divide by zero type of bug going on in there&#xD;
which corrupted movement results, causing the 20k death result.&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;Cheers,&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Thu, 28 Sep 2006 14:46:40 GMT</pubDate>
