      <title>Demi-Plane of Blood changes</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&amp;message.id=11859#M11859</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana size=2&gt;The following changes to the Demi-Plane of Blood will go live on the same day that Prophecy of Ro launches.&amp;nbsp; There were far too many changes to list in the patch message, so they have been listed in their entirety here.&amp;nbsp; Most changes were meant to address bugs or loopholes in raids.&amp;nbsp; A few changes were to address difficulty.&amp;nbsp; The most important change was to add&amp;nbsp;bonuses I had intended to include in the zone&amp;nbsp;from the&amp;nbsp;beginning,&amp;nbsp;but&amp;nbsp;was unable to&amp;nbsp;in time for Darkhollow's launch.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana size=2&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana size=2&gt;Redfang:&lt;BR&gt;The blooddrinker bats will no longer assign themselves as pets to Redfang. This is what was causing him to auto-aggro when he respawned.&amp;nbsp; Though it might be tempting to avoid re-aggroing him to take a reprieve from the fight, there are &lt;EM&gt;serious&lt;/EM&gt; drawbacks to leaving Redfang up unaggroed for too long.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Zi-thuuli:&lt;BR&gt;Nothing.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Hatchet:&lt;BR&gt;Hatchet will continue to "chase" people all the way down to 10% health.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Previously he would stop using this hazard after he had been&amp;nbsp;trapped four times.&lt;BR&gt;If Hatchet goes prone, he can no longer follow through with any axe tosses that may be pending. A message will indicate this to the affected player.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Sisters:&lt;BR&gt;The bats near the bedrooms are now part of this event. They will only spawn when the Sisters event is activated, and they'll deactivate&amp;nbsp;after successfully completing the event.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Tris:&lt;BR&gt;Increased hit points slightly.&lt;BR&gt;Increased the rate at which she changes forms slightly.&lt;BR&gt;The chest should no longer have a chance to double&amp;nbsp;or triple spawn on a win if multiple priests landed a cure spell simultaneously.&lt;BR&gt;Some of the werewolf adds are no longer mezzable.&lt;BR&gt;The orc adds will now walk in the room with Tris instead of bunching up outside.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Devlin:&lt;BR&gt;Changed the pathing in Devlin's room and increased his height. His pathing appears to be MUCH better.&lt;BR&gt;As an additional safety precaution, added a tether to Devlin that will teleport him back to his room if he strays too far away from spawn.&lt;BR&gt;When Devlin throws a bottle at someone, a text warning will now display to everyone nearby, similar to the message that you see when Hatchet is about to chase someone.&lt;BR&gt;Fixed the problem with Devlin's&amp;nbsp;adds not depopping on success&amp;nbsp;or failure.&lt;BR&gt;When Devlin's shield is broken, he'll now wield a broken shield (no graphic) in his offhand. This will prevent him from gaining DPS due to dual wield. I hope this will promote breaking the shield, whereas before guilds may have avoided it due to the drawback.&lt;BR&gt;Mana Weave no longer counts as a fire spell for breaking Devlin's shield.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Roley:&lt;BR&gt;Roley and Adrianna now spawn at a static location in the ballroom, which should help prevent initial&amp;nbsp;warping at the beginning of the event.&lt;BR&gt;As an additional safety precaution, added a tether to Roley and Adrianna that will warp them back to their room if they stray too far away from spawn. This will help mitigate warping, but also means they must be fought in the ballroom.&lt;BR&gt;The chests will no longer cast their 'fine red mist' trap if hit by a stray AE spell.&lt;BR&gt;The twitching skeleton NPC in the lab no longer spawns.&lt;BR&gt;As mentioned above, the bats in the bedrooms are now part of the Sister's event and will not interfere with the Roley event.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Performer:&lt;BR&gt;Blueblood and the Spinstress are immune to Song of Highsun.&lt;BR&gt;Removed the drops from the adds in this event so corpses won't litter the room and contribute to lag.&lt;BR&gt;The Performer is now rooted in place.&lt;BR&gt;Less adds will spawn, per wave, in the later phases of the event.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Mayong:&lt;BR&gt;Increased attack speed slightly.&lt;BR&gt;The named gargoyles will now respawn properly between attempts.&lt;BR&gt;Zombie and drachnid trash mobs should no longer path high enough to add while fighting Mayong.&lt;BR&gt;Mayong's AE slash ability will now correctly hit the people closest to him instead of killing everyone not close to him.&lt;BR&gt;Fixed the typo in Mayong's hail text.&lt;BR&gt;You no longer need to sneak to speak to Mayong and trigger the encounter.&lt;BR&gt;It should now be more obvious what your choices meant when triggering the Mayong fight.&lt;BR&gt;Bonus rewards for killing Mayong are now in.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;General Changes:&lt;BR&gt;The spinstun screech spell now has half the arc width as before and decreased duration.&lt;BR&gt;All four flags received for doing the AE blocker quest will now show up on EQ players profiles, and the descriptions should make more sense.&lt;BR&gt;The dinner invitation will now be added to your keyring when you click the statue in West Korlach.&lt;BR&gt;Fixed the typo when you click into Demi-Plane after killing Mayong.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana size=2&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana size=2&gt;Happy launch day!&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT face=Verdana size=2&gt;-Prathun&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
