      <title>Video Blanking Out or East/West bug</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&amp;message.id=9344#M9344</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;When this bug occurs you see only&amp;nbsp;sky, particles, and the UI. It often goes in and out as you rotate around, and "blanks" when facing a certain direction, like east or west.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I did fix one bug that was causing this in several zones, and that is why I closed the previous thread. However, it appears that there is still a remaining bug, so this thread is to get information.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Please only post in this thread if you have experienced the bug (and only the bug described above)&amp;nbsp;since the last live patch (7/2005). If you have some other bug please post in the tech support forum or on another appropriate thread.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I'd like to know the answers to these questions:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1. What zone were you in when it occured, and the /loc if you have it.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2. What video card you have, and what driver version if you know it.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3. Do you have HardwareTnL=True or False in your eqclient.ini?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4. In advanced display options:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;a.&amp;nbsp;Hardware Vertex Shaders on?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;b.&amp;nbsp;Pixel Shader 1.1 on?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;c.&amp;nbsp;Pixel Shader 1.4 on?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;d.&amp;nbsp;Pixel Shader 2.0 on?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;e.&amp;nbsp;Advanced Lighting on?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Also, if you have any other details about this bug such as it always happens when you do some particular thing, or always after some event, please add that.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
